title: EPC names girls volleyball all-stars; Becahi's Jordan Young repeats as MVP
text:
By Kyle Craig | For lehighvalleylive.com on October 19, 2015 6:10 PM View/Post Comments 
For the second consecutive year, Bethlehem Catholic’s Jordan Young has been recognized as the Eastern Pennsylvania Conference’s Most Valuable Player. 
Young, a senior outside hitter and George Washington University recruit, received the honor as the conference’s coaches selected their 2015 all-stars. 
Parkland led the way with four first-team selections. 
Here’s the complete breakdown of honorees, as selected by the coaches:
